name: RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR
description: Error codes of the RTMP or RTMPS streaming.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_OK: The RTMP or RTMPS streaming publishes successfully.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_INVALID_ARGUME: Invalid argument used. Please check the parameter setting. For example, if you do not call setLiveTranscoding to set the transcoding parameters before calling addPublishStreamUrl, the SDK returns this error.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_ENCRYPTED_STRE: Check whether you set the parameters in the setLiveTranscoding method properly.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_CONNECTION_TIM: The RTMP or RTMPS streaming is encrypted and cannot be published. Call addPublishStreamUrl to re-publish the stream.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_INTERNAL_SERVE: An error occurs in Agora's streaming server. Call the addPublishStreamUrl method to publish the streaming again.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_RTMP_SERVER_ER: An error occurs in the CDN server.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_TOO_OFTEN: The RTMP or RTMPS streaming publishes too frequently.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_REACH_LIMIT: The host has published more than 10 URLs. Delete the unnecessary URLs before adding new ones.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_NOT_AUTHORIZED: The host manipulates other hosts' streams. For example, the host updates or stops other hosts' streams. Check your app logic.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_STREAM_NOT_FOU: Agora's server fails to find the RTMP or RTMPS streaming.

parameters.RTMP_STREAM_PUBLISH_ERROR_FORMAT_NOT_SUP: The URL format is incorrect. Check whether the URL format is correct.
